{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/blog/2011-03-07-Strobist-Lighting-102-12-Position-Distance/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Rob Li.co"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"c67e7492-3e65-590b-846b-f28529a95ad6","excerpt":"Since photography is all about light, my goal over the next 18 months is to become very competent with lighting (SB-900 purchased, well, gifted (20)!).  Luckily…","html":"<p>Since photography is all about light, my goal over the next 18 months is to become very competent with lighting (SB-900 purchased, well, gifted (20)!).  Luckily, there are great, free resources online like <a href=\"http://strobist.blogspot.com/\">http://strobist.blogspot.com/ aka David Hobby aka Strobist</a></p>\n<p>So on with the learning (new category added).</p>\n<hr>\n<p><a href=\"http://strobist.blogspot.com/2007/06/lighting-102-12-position-distance.html\">http://strobist.blogspot.com/2007/06/lighting-102-12-position-distance.html</a></p>\n<p>The main lesson from this was that you control lighting “depth of field” by varying the distance between the flash and the subject and background.  The relative differences cause fall-off to be much more noticeable on the background because of the inverse square law of light.</p>\n<p>\n    </p><figure>\n        <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 630px; \">\n      <a class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\" href=\"/co-robli-dev/static/0edc5bb215dc6a511bbe9a4c0834ed9d/4b190/2011-03-07-at-22-58-03-_dsc0851.jpg\" style=\"display: block\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 66.45569620253164%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/jpeg;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" alt=\"2011 03 07 at 22 58 03  dsc0851\" title=\"2011 03 07 at 22 58 03  dsc0851\" src=\"/co-robli-dev/static/0edc5bb215dc6a511bbe9a4c0834ed9d/828fb/2011-03-07-at-22-58-03-_dsc0851.jpg\" srcset=\"/co-robli-dev/static/0edc5bb215dc6a511bbe9a4c0834ed9d/ff44c/2011-03-07-at-22-58-03-_dsc0851.jpg 158w,\n/co-robli-dev/static/0edc5bb215dc6a511bbe9a4c0834ed9d/a6688/2011-03-07-at-22-58-03-_dsc0851.jpg 315w,\n/co-robli-dev/static/0edc5bb215dc6a511bbe9a4c0834ed9d/828fb/2011-03-07-at-22-58-03-_dsc0851.jpg 630w,\n/co-robli-dev/static/0edc5bb215dc6a511bbe9a4c0834ed9d/4b190/2011-03-07-at-22-58-03-_dsc0851.jpg 800w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 630px) 100vw, 630px\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\" loading=\"lazy\">\n  </a>\n    </span>\n        <figcaption>Subject and background relatively close together when considering distance from flash</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n<p></p>\n<p>\n    </p><figure>\n        <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 630px; \">\n      <a class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\" href=\"/co-robli-dev/static/ef9c12e32a42ce705bd637e44e2e4017/4b190/2011-03-07-at-22-58-24-_dsc0852.jpg\" style=\"display: block\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 66.45569620253164%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/jpeg;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" alt=\"2011 03 07 at 22 58 24  dsc0852\" title=\"2011 03 07 at 22 58 24  dsc0852\" src=\"/co-robli-dev/static/ef9c12e32a42ce705bd637e44e2e4017/828fb/2011-03-07-at-22-58-24-_dsc0852.jpg\" srcset=\"/co-robli-dev/static/ef9c12e32a42ce705bd637e44e2e4017/ff44c/2011-03-07-at-22-58-24-_dsc0852.jpg 158w,\n/co-robli-dev/static/ef9c12e32a42ce705bd637e44e2e4017/a6688/2011-03-07-at-22-58-24-_dsc0852.jpg 315w,\n/co-robli-dev/static/ef9c12e32a42ce705bd637e44e2e4017/828fb/2011-03-07-at-22-58-24-_dsc0852.jpg 630w,\n/co-robli-dev/static/ef9c12e32a42ce705bd637e44e2e4017/4b190/2011-03-07-at-22-58-24-_dsc0852.jpg 800w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 630px) 100vw, 630px\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\" loading=\"lazy\">\n  </a>\n    </span>\n        <figcaption>Subject and background becoming relatively further apart</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n<p></p>\n<p>\n    </p><figure>\n        <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 630px; \">\n      <a class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\" href=\"/co-robli-dev/static/d2612da1488e28a7507ba0348440b286/4b190/2011-03-07-at-22-58-36-_dsc0853.jpg\" style=\"display: block\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 66.45569620253164%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/jpeg;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" alt=\"2011 03 07 at 22 58 36  dsc0853\" title=\"2011 03 07 at 22 58 36  dsc0853\" src=\"/co-robli-dev/static/d2612da1488e28a7507ba0348440b286/828fb/2011-03-07-at-22-58-36-_dsc0853.jpg\" srcset=\"/co-robli-dev/static/d2612da1488e28a7507ba0348440b286/ff44c/2011-03-07-at-22-58-36-_dsc0853.jpg 158w,\n/co-robli-dev/static/d2612da1488e28a7507ba0348440b286/a6688/2011-03-07-at-22-58-36-_dsc0853.jpg 315w,\n/co-robli-dev/static/d2612da1488e28a7507ba0348440b286/828fb/2011-03-07-at-22-58-36-_dsc0853.jpg 630w,\n/co-robli-dev/static/d2612da1488e28a7507ba0348440b286/4b190/2011-03-07-at-22-58-36-_dsc0853.jpg 800w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 630px) 100vw, 630px\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\" loading=\"lazy\">\n  </a>\n    </span>\n        <figcaption>Subject and background relatively far apart</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n<p></p>\n<p>My exposure of the subject was not consistent because I didn’t bother being too accurate with flash power and camera aperture settings.  The principle is there though and an important lesson well learnt.</p>\n<p>For a bit of fun I did put the speedlight to 1/1 power, zoomed to 200mm and did a test shot…I wasn’t dumb enough to point it at me, but even at the wall it knocked me out. What power!  Excellent tool.</p>","frontmatter":{"title":"Strobist: Lighting 102: 1.2 - Position | Distance","date":"March 07, 2011","description":null}},"previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/2011-04-10-Learning-lighting-vacuum-cleaner/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Learning lighting - vacuum cleaner"}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/2011-02-21-Post-processing-and-creative-process/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Post processing and creative process"}}},"pageContext":{"id":"c67e7492-3e65-590b-846b-f28529a95ad6","previousPostId":"3bf37127-1336-5451-aa42-19b84f7ab519","nextPostId":"fc4dabec-a1a3-5c68-82c2-5e00d37e172a"}},"staticQueryHashes":["2841359383","916993862"]}